reviews.text: A bit disappointed to find out they don’t serve soup noodle during dinner time. Ordered red curry with beef brisket and tendon, and stirred fried Chinese kale with salted fish. Red curry tasted good, except the tendon was overcooked and mushy. The Chinese kale wasn’t that good and tasted fishy, likely because of the not so good salted fish. Service was quite good though. Overall, it’s a just ok dinner experience.
